Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)

In ll_direct_IO_26() we have:

        /* 0. Need locking between buffered and direct access. and race with
         *    size changing by concurrent truncates and writes.
         * 1. Need inode mutex to operate transient pages.
         */
        if (rw == READ)
                mutex_lock(&inode->i_mutex);

So llite is relying on i_mutex to mutually exclude direct read against write/truncate. If we are changing locking requirement for write, do we need to worry about here as well?
